    <title>On the $\ell_1$-Norm Minimization
   Problem for Sparse Recovery in Über-Complete Dictionaries</title>
    <summary>  This paper studies the $\ell_1$-norm minimization problem
   for sparse recovery.  We show that über-complete dictionaries
   with unicode characters like café and naïve
  can still be handled robustly.
  </summary>
